---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
---

<Base title="Privacy policy" description="What data this site collects, what it doesn't, and your rights.">
  <section class="wrap prose">
    <h1 class="page-title">Privacy policy</h1>
    <p class="small muted">Last updated: July 2026</p>

    <p>
      {SITE.name} ({SITE.domain}) is a static website run by an independent publisher. I keep
      data collection to the minimum needed to run the site, and I don't sell or share your
      data. This page explains what is processed, why, and what rights you have.
    </p>

    <h2>Who is responsible</h2>
    <p>
      This site is operated by an independent publisher who acts as the data controller for
      the limited processing described below. For any privacy question or request, contact
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>What I collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Nothing you type.</strong> This site has no accounts, no comments, and no
        forms. I never ask for or store your personal information through the site.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Basic, anonymous server data.</strong> The site is served through Cloudflare,
        which processes standard server logs — such as IP address, browser type, and the pages
        requested — to deliver the site and protect it from abuse and attacks. Cloudflare acts
        as a data processor on my behalf, and as a global network it may process this data on
        servers outside your country. See
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Cloudflare's privacy policy</a>.
        <!-- 如果以后加了分析工具(如 Cloudflare Web Analytics / Plausible / GA4),在这里补一节说明:
             收集什么、是否用 cookie、是否需要 cookie 同意横幅。GA4 会设 cookie,面向欧盟访客需要同意横幅;
             Plausible / Cloudflare Web Analytics 无 cookie,通常无需横幅。-->
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Legal basis (for EU/UK visitors)</h2>
    <p>
      Under the GDPR and UK GDPR, the limited server-log processing above relies on my
      <strong>legitimate interest</strong> in operating a secure, functioning website. It is not
      used to build profiles of you or to track you across other sites. Because this site sets no
      analytics or advertising cookies of its own, no cookie-consent banner is required at this time.
    </p>

    <h2>How long data is kept</h2>
    <p>
      I do not maintain my own server logs. Cloudflare retains standard logs for a limited period
      under its own retention schedule (see its privacy policy above). Emails you send me are kept
      only as long as needed to handle your message.
    </p>

    <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
    <p>
      Some outbound links are affiliate links. When you click one, the destination site may set
      its own cookies to attribute the referral. Those cookies belong to the provider's site and
      are governed by their privacy policy, not mine. See my
      <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">affiliate disclosure</a> for how this works and how I make money.
    </p>

    <h2>Email</h2>
    <p>
      If you email me at <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>, I use
      your address only to reply.I will never add you to a mailing list unless you deliberately sign up for one, and I never share or sell your address to anyone.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on where you live (for example under the GDPR in the EU/UK, or the CCPA in
      California), you may have the right to access, correct, or delete personal data relating to
      you, and to object to certain processing. Since this site stores no personal data of its own
      beyond any email you choose to send, most requests can be handled quickly — just contact
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      This site is intended for a general adult audience and is not directed at children under 13.
      I do not knowingly collect data from children.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>Any change to this policy will be posted on this page with an updated date.</p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-title { padding-top: 2rem; }
</style>
